column4: <content>The painting attrib. by Glück to M. van Cleve is in the same sense as the drawing, but whereas the engraving (v.B. 205) is reversed it follows the drawing exactly, while the painting differs greatly in many details: [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. It is not at all certain whether the painting is by M. van Cleve. Treatment of space different and many additional and different figures, compositional changes. The Team of horses and man on the front horse, his position (head turned inwards) closer to Albertina drawing of team of horses (pl. 105).</content>

<part_of.title>Catalogue de tableaux anciens, Nouvelles acquisitions Juin-Août 1938, Kunsthandel P. de Boer, Amsterdam; [Notitie FG op titelpagina]: 'N° 11 M. van Cleve; [Inlegblaadje] 11 Maerten van Cleve, Anvers 1527-1581, Grande vue sur la ville d'Anvers avec la porte St. George, bois 106 x 148 cm. Gustav Glück pense que le tableau a été peint par M.v. Cleve d'après un dessin de P. Breughel le Vieux [...]; [Notitie FG]: ' see P. De Boer, Helsche en Fluweelen Brueghels, P. de Boer, A'dam 1934, N° 108, pl. 19.'</part_of.title>
